DoverNet Wants In-Car Computing to Become More Affordable

February 09, 2018

DoverNet announced the launch of its DoverNet Interactive Mobile Data terminals, which are equipped with a built-in speech engine, allowing in-uniformed officers to use the device as their primary eCitation system.

Officers are now capable of capturing detailed events on-site without the hassle of entering their devices in and out of the vehicle. The interactive displays have been designed using Microsoft 3D touch software, making them easier to use. In the long run, this allows emergency goods partners and officers to save money and time.
